#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "> Proof of work is a way to legitimize untrusted party\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "What exactly is proof of work?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:11
msgid ""
"Proof of work is a cryptographic proof that untrusted party committed "
"significant computational resources to solve artificial problem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:13
msgid "Technically, the \"proof\" is simply a solution to the problem at hand."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "It's all about legitimizing untrusted party"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:17
msgid ""
"How an untrusted party on the Internet could earn any level of your trust?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:19
msgid ""
"It can prove its commitment by solving agreed computationally hard problem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:21
msgid ""
"For example, by requiring untrusted party to perform a hard computation "
"before you accept their connection, you limit connections only to "
"\"committed\" parties."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:23
msgid ""
"In another example, you could require PoW to be attached to incoming e-mails "
"to make spam prohibitively expensive."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "Work must be otherwise useless"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:27
msgid ""
"The work on and solution to \"computationally hard problem\" cannot be "
"useful in any other way than to prove the commitment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:29
msgid ""
"If the work is useful elsewhere then it doesn't prove commitment to you."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:31
msgid ""
"The problem must be artificial. Otherwise incentives are skewed and the "
"whole scheme breaks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Strong asymmetry"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:35
msgid ""
"The requirement for proof of work scheme is strong asymmetry for work vs "
"verification resources."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "The work must be arbitrarily hard. At the same time proof verification must remain dirt cheap (in terms of computational resources).  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/what-is-pow.md:39
msgid ""
"Cheap verification is critical because at this stage we are dealing with "
"potentially huge number of untrusted parties, who could DoS the verifier by "
"submitting invalid proofs. Such proofs should be trivial to discard."
msgstr ""
